parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cable can cause unexpected and sudden acceleration, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The throttle jams into high-rev
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly to high speed
the throttle cable breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause unexpected acceleration, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control resumes by itself
causing acceleration
the cruise control is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and popping can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the transmission, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission pops into gear when shifting into drive
the transmission shifts and pops when accelerating from 20 mph
the transmission fails to engage properly in reverse gear
the transmission fails altogether
requiring replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat assembly can cause the seat to not lock in the full forward position, affecting the driver's comfort and visibility, which can lead to accidents or discomfort while driving.
symptoms: The seat does not lock in the full forward position
the seat moves forward and backward excessively
the seat is too soft
the driver sinks down in the seat
poor vision due to seat position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a sudden loss of brake power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the vehicle has extended stopping distances
the brake warning light comes on
the vehicle has no brakes or reduced braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries. In extreme cases, fires can spread to the passenger compartment, putting occupants at risk.
symptoms: Smoke or flames visible from the engine compartment
burning smell
overheating engine
loss of engine power
warning lights or alarms on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water pump failure can cause engine overheating, leading to damage to the engine, cylinder head, and other components. In extreme cases, engine failure can occur, leaving the driver stranded or causing accidents.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
overheating engine
temperature gauge rising
warning lights or alarms on the dashboard
whining or grinding noise from the water pump.
